i around 9600 \\AA and a small contribution\nof FeH, but we cannot confirm a detection of TiH in the spectra of cool L\nsubdwarfs. High resolution spectroscopy has aided in beginning to understand\nthe complex molecular chemistry in metal-deficient and ultralow-mass objects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2005 17:59:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
